// useDesignCanvas
// Initializes the CanvasKit/Skia WebGL surface and drives RAF-batched rendering for the design editor canvas.

Rendering is triggered reactively when renderVersion or selectedIds change in the editor store.
A ResizeObserver handles canvas resizes by recreating the WebGL surface at the new dimensions.
On unmount, all animation frames are cancelled and editor refs are destroyed.

FUNCTION useDesignCanvas() -> { canvasRef, isLoading, error, hitTestSectionTitle, hitTestComponentLabel }  EXPORT
  CALLS: getCanvasKit (canvaskit), SkiaRenderer (renderer), initEditorRefs (designEditorRefs),
         destroyEditorRefs (designEditorRefs), getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs),
         useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore)
  Manages state: isLoading, error.
  On mount, loads CanvasKit WASM, creates a WebGL surface, instantiates the SkiaRenderer, and loads fonts.
  Subscribes to renderVersion and selectedIds to schedule repaints via scheduleRender.
  Sets up a ResizeObserver that recreates the surface whenever the canvas element is resized.

---

FUNCTION renderNow()
  CALLS: getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs)
  Reads current pan, zoom, viewport size, and scene state from the editor store and refs.
  Passes everything to the renderer to draw a single frame, including selection, hover, marquee, snap guides,
  rotation preview, drop target, layout insert indicator, pen state, and remote cursors.

---

FUNCTION scheduleRender()
  If no animation frame is already queued, requests one and calls renderNow when it fires.

---

FUNCTION hitTestSectionTitle(canvasX, canvasY) -> SceneNode | null
  CALLS: getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs)
  Delegates to the renderer's section title hit test using the current scene graph.

---

FUNCTION hitTestComponentLabel(canvasX, canvasY) -> SceneNode | null
  CALLS: getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs)
  Delegates to the renderer's component label hit test using the current scene graph.
